This paper presents an extension of a machine reading comprehension model, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with information retrieval, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which could suggest cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category.
